  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Frameworks\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) compliance requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting (SAR) protocols\n\n3. Key Strategies\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Implementing strict identification procedures\n- Establishing financial transaction tracking mechanisms\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Central banks\n- Government financial oversight agencies\n\n5. Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n\nThese frameworks aim to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds and integrating them into legitimate financial systems.",
